                     <interp inst="t18210214-74-person834" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I know this confession to be signed by the Magistrate, and saw the prisoner sign it. The watch is worth 12 s.</p>
               <p>(read.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210214-74-person835">
                  Edward 
                  Oliver
               <interp inst="t18210214-74-person835" type="surname" value="Oliver"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210214-74-person835" type="given" value="Edward"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210214-74-person835" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             confesses that, he stole the watch, and took it to Mr. King's, the pawnbrokers, but he was not at home; he then took it to Mr. Clark's, and sold it to his son for 6 s. He took 5 s. home to his mother, and told her he got it from a gentleman, for holding his horse.</p>
